stickerText:
You fall in love with a baby with the
cutest little fat folds
and then bam, they’re gone but it’s okay
because in its place is a toddler with the greatest laugh on earth
And then one day the toddler’s gone
and in its place a little kid that asks the most interesting questions you’ve ever heard
And this keeps going on like that but you never get the chance to miss any of them
because there’s always a new kid to take the place of the old
Until they grow up… then, in a moment…
All those kids you fell in love with walk out the door at the same time
like the expression, you never know the last time you’ll pick up your kid

stickerText: EASY DINNER IDEA

CROCKPOT
CAJUN ALFREDO
(recipe in caption)

contents.desc: This slow cooker alfredo is dairy free but if youre not, just use heavy cream in place of coconut milk! #easydinner #easyrecipe #weeknightdinner #crockpot #slowcooker #lazygirldinner #thatmom #lazymom #dairyfree

Mix 1 lb uncooked cajun sausage, 3c chicken broth, 1/2 can coconut milk, 2T nutritional yeast, 1/2c shredded parmesan, 1T cajun seasoning, minced garlic and dried minced onion to taste in the crockpot. Cook on low for 4 hours. Set crockpot to high and add 3 cups of uncooked pasta. Cook for ~30 minutes. Dont overcook the pasta! Optional: for a thicker sauce, mix 1tsp of cornstarch with 2tsp of cold water and then add to the crockpot.

7191957156042837294.desc: 4 russet potatoes, cut into 1” pieces 1/2 diced sweet onion or dried onion 1 tbsp minced garlic 1 tbsp @countrycrock plant butter 1 tbsp oil 1/2 tsp paprika 1 tsp salt Pepper to taste 2 cans of chicken broth 1 can of coconut milk 1/2 cup nutritional yeast Optional: Liquid smoke Lemon juice Bacon bits 1. Melt butter in a pot with oil. Sauté onions until translucent. Add garlic and cook for one minute.  2. Add potatoes, paprika, salt, and pepper and sauté for a few minutes.  3. Add chicken broth, coconut milk, and nutritional yeast. Add 1 tsp liquid smoke (optional). Stir to combine. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.  4. Add 1/2 tsp of lemon juice (optional but makes it taste cheesier). Serve as is or use an immersion blender to blend some of the potatoes to make it creamier.  5.
